The course will include a thorough discussion of youth participation as a goal and method, and a discussion on the impact of youth inclusion in society. Development of competences to increase youth participation and inclusion.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The student evaluates young people's participation as a basis for youth work and plans activities to involve young people and support their own initiative.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student:  - understands the concept of youth participation, the purpose of participation and the method in youth work; - defines the basis for active citizenship;  - analyses participation opportunities for young people, including youth associations, youth councils, etc.; - assesses the bases and methods for involving young people in the planning, implementation and evaluation of youth work;  - values the support and development of youth initiative and entrepreneurial civic mind-set.
